Come trial a new dance style! Learn the basics of hip hop and body isolation movement with this high energy course! Students will learn choreographed sequences to their favourite hip hop and pop music as they focus on picking up new steps, expressing themselves, and having fun!

Share the joy of movement and dance with your little one! Parents and tots move to the beat to develop coordination and a sense of rhythm. Come shake your sillies out! Adult supervision and participation required.

Allow your child to express themselves through dance by exploring the basics of ballet! This course will give students an introduction to ballet techniques with focus on movement, balance and basic steps. Students will learn coordination, flexibility, body awareness in a fun and encouraging environment. At the end of the session students will do a final performance to show off their new skills!

Allow your child to express themselves through dance by exploring the basics of ballet and jazz! Ballet is the basis of many dance styles. This course will give students an introduction to ballet techniques with focus on movement, balance and basic steps. Students will also work on expressive movement, flexibility, and jazz steps in a fun and encouraging environment. At the end of the session students will do a final performance to show off their new skills!

Thich Nhat Hanh’s Plum Village community defines mindfulness as a state of mind “we generate when we bring our mind back to our body and get in touch with what is going on in the present moment, within us and around us. We become aware of our breathing and come home to our body, fully present for ourselves and whatever we are doing.” Mindfulness allows us to slow down and take in each moment of our day in this fast-paced and ever changing world. In this weekly mediation class with Aaron Roth, we will practice sitting mindfulness meditation (focusing using our breath), bell meditation, and also walking meditation. Instruction and guidance will be provided.  This practice is good for all levels of meditation experience.

NO CLASS NOV 11

NOTE: A meditation cushion or chair is highly recommended for this practice.

EXPERIENCE 
This course is great for beginners and those with previous experience looking to improve their skills. 

ACCESSIBILITY
Please email cityartscentre@edmonton.ca in advance to notify programmers of any accessibility needs or desired accommodations that you may have for participating in this program and we will work to support your requests within our capacity. 

ABSENCES & CANCELLATIONS
Please note that make-up classes are not provided and you should plan accordingly before registering. For further information regarding the cancellation procedures call 311.

Start your Sunday morning off right with a meditation "sampler pack" at one of the most beautiful spots in Edmonton.  During this six week class, Aaron Roth will facilitate six different kinds of meditation practice for all levels of experience in the pyramids of the Muttart Conservatory. Enjoy practicing Mindfulness Meditation, Zazen (Zen Meditation), Guided Meditation, Guided Imagery, Metta Meditation (Loving Kindness), and Walking Meditation.
NOTE: A meditation cushion or chair is highly recommended for this practice.

EXPERIENCE 
This course is great for beginners and those with previous experience looking to improve their skills. 

ACCESSIBILITY
Please email cityartscentre@edmonton.ca in advance to notify programmers of any accessibility needs or desired accommodations that you may have for participating in this program and we will work to support your requests within our capacity. 

ABSENCES & CANCELLATIONS
Please note that make-up classes are not provided and you should plan accordingly before registering. For further information regarding the cancellation procedures call 311.
coursetitle: Sunday Morning Meditation at Muttart Conservatory

coursedesc:
So many of the things we do in our daily lives add tension and stress. One of the ways of thinking about meditation is that it is an undoing and a return to an inner peacefulness that we have lost touch with in our busy, stressful lives. In this 6 week course with Michelle Johnston you will learn the foundations of mindfulness practice: body, breath, emotions and mind. You will begin to use these tools of meditation to access inner peacefulness. Please bring a yoga mat and a blanket.

EXPERIENCE 
This course is great for beginners and those with previous experience looking to improve their skills. 

ACCESSIBILITY
Please email cityartscentre@edmonton.ca in advance to notify programmers of any accessibility needs or desired accommodations that you may have for participating in this program and we will work to support your requests within our capacity. 

ABSENCES & CANCELLATIONS
Please note that make-up classes are not provided and you should plan accordingly before registering. For further information regarding the cancellation procedures call 311.

Welcome to the world of movement! In this creative non-parented program, preschoolers will have fun navigating the world of obstacles and dance. Through imaginative play and self-discovery, children will enhance their physical and social skills while increasing their self-confidence.

READY...SET...GO! This high energy program will be filled with various games, crafts and activities; as we explore the jungle and the ways animals move in it. Children will be introduced to the basic movement skills such as running, jumping, crawling, kicking, throwing and catching that are essential to physical activity and sport.

In this Ready2 program, we will hone in on each child's hand-eye coordination and their ability to catch, throw, kick and aim. These are some of the skills required for sports such as basketball, football, soccer and baseball. We'll have a ball learning proper techniques and progressing each participant through the skills in a fun environment. Games, crafts and a variety of activities will be introduced. Let’s play ball!

In this Ready2 play program, your child will unlock the superhero inside of them. Various games, crafts and activities themed around their favorite superheroes will give your child the chance to develop their confidence through play. This program provides the space and materials for your child to use their imaginations to the fullest and have fun with fellow superhero friends.

In this Ready2 program, preschoolers will run freely in an activity filled and fun environment. We will test their endurance and learn proper running techniques that will be essential for continuation in a variety of physical activity and sports. A variety of games, crafts and activities will be introduced. So tie up those sneakers and catch me if you can!

In this twice a week program we will run an alphabet and numerical marathon as we work on developing both fine and gross motor skills in your preschooler. In a fun filled environment, each class will include crafts, songs, games, physical activity and basic movement skills as we explore the different letters and numbers.

This Learn to Play program is designed to get you hooked on this increasingly popular sport and ready to join the City’s Drop-in Pickleball program! By combining elements of badminton, tennis and table tennis Pickleball is a great activity for all ages. Participants will be taught the skills, rules and strategies of Pickleball by a certified sport-specific instructor. Come out and learn one of the fastest growing sports in a fun and friendly environment. Equipment is provided by the City of Edmonton.

Are you an experienced potter looking for studio time to improve and hone your skills? Do you have projects you want to complete and need access to equipment and facilities? Make time in your busy life for your creative practice with this dedicated studio time. Work on your own self directed projects at your own pace and enjoy the shared cameradie of other artists in the studio. Pottery Studio for Seniors sessions are available to provide time and space for those 55+ who have taken many classes and identify as knowledgeable and experienced. Individuals must be knowledgeable in pottery studio practices and procedures and can work independently as no instruction is provided. 

Individuals must bring their own medium fire cone 6 clay from Plainsman Clay and their own tools; no other clay is permitted. Slips, glazes, and firing are included. 

These sessions are only available for seniors ages 55+ who have extensive pottery experience (from the ACT Seniors Pottery Sessions) and can work by themselves. If you are unsure of your experience level please contact cityartscentre@edmonton.ca before registering.

Take your pottery skills to the next level by learning how to throw, decorate, and glaze porcelain-like clay. Create handmade projects that will be lighter, finer, and more translucent. 
Expand on your existing skills in centering, altering, trimming, and decorating thrown pots while learning new techniques and experimenting with style and design. Learn from talented ceramic artist Kaleb Romano of how to throw sets, create complex forms, and to push your imagination while working with clay. Discover creative methods of surface decoration including image transfer, resist, mishima, and sgraffito. 

A basic set of pottery tools is required and can be found for approximately $15 - 35 at local art stores. Tools required specially for wheel throwing: ribs, clay wire, sponge, pin tool, sculpting wood knives, etc. Clay, slips, glazes and firing are provided. Underglazes are available for minimal testing, but individuals will need to purchase their own for extensive project use.

Experience a classical art form by sculpting the human figure by working with live models. In this eight week course use the medium of clay to explore the anatomy of the human body and successfully create multiple figurative sculptures. Guided by artist and sculptor Ritchie Velthuis learn step by step techniques to achieve success and to take away the intimidation of working with figurative subject matter. By sculpting from life by referencing a live model you will develop a sense of proportion, 3D design, and capture unique and individual qualities while finding your own sculpture style. Finished work is done in medium fire-stoneware. 


Clay and firing are included. A basic set of pottery tools is required and can be found for approximately $15 - 35 at local art stores. Tools required specially for sculpting: felting knives, clay wire, sponge, pin tool, wood tools, etc.

This program is for novice cross-country skiers who want to get off on the right track this winter! Participants will learn the basics of classical technique; striding, stopping, turning, uphill/downhill skills, and how to fall safely. Create your own hand carved cards that you can give away to all your favourite people! In this comprehensive 8 week class learn the fundamentals and history of two of the world's newest and most delightful forms of art.  Comics and cartoons! You will learn to apply the fundamentals of drafting to human forms, as well as animals, backgrounds, and wildly imaginative characters.  Whether the stories you want to tell are filled with whimsy and joy or are gritty this course is designed to teach you how to get your story onto paper using the tried and trued methods and techniques established by the great pioneers of the cartooning form. Each of week artist Nickolas MacKay will demonstrate and showcase a different focus and by the end of the session you will have explored the concepts of: faces, bodies, backgrounds, colouring, character design, animals, working with liquid ink, and storytelling with paneling.  Additionally, the culture of comics and cartoons stretches around the globe and in this class you will have the opportunity to explore iconic examples of the types of comics and cartoons produced by both the eastern and the western world throughout the whole of the arts history.
If a picture is worth a thousand words, imagine the stories you can tell with comics!

Discover the colours of winter in this informative workshop where you will experience demonstrations and lots of exercises to learn just how to make colorful winter scenes.  Using a paint-a-long class format with Artist Frank Haddock you will be taken through the various stages of your painting from start to finish while adding your special flourish to your own masterpiece. 
Don’t miss this chance to make a neat painting for a special friend!

ALL MATERIALS ARE INCLUDED, just bring yourself & your creativity. 
EXPERIENCE
Some previous painting experience is necessary, this course is ideal for those wanting to add to their skills

coursetitle: The Hidden Colours of Winter with Watercolours: Landscape Workshop

coursedesc:
Love watercolours but you have never taken a drawing or painting class? No problem, this class is for all skill levels, taking you to the next step in the process. Use watercolor pencils and ink to draw and sketch landscapes, animals, and people. Artist Julie Drew will show you numerous techniques to combine a variety of watercolour methods and even have you explore working outdoors with plein air sessions (weather permitting) Sharpen your observation skill, experiment with compositions, and capture a mood, a place, and an idea with your artwork. 

All supplies are included; an email will be sent out 3 days prior to the program start date to confirm the class. 

EXPERIENCE 
This course is great for beginners and those with previous experience looking to improve their skills.

Spend a wonderful afternoon painting those rich and warm colours that you find during autumn. Create a special fall scene with colourful leaves in large trees featuring a backdrop of a crisp autumn sky.  Enjoy a paint-a-long format with artist Frank Haddock as he demonstrates each step and allows you time to learn and paint your own individualized fall scene. During this one afternoon workshop you will experience informative and attentive instruction as well as creating a masterpiece to treasure. If you are a beginner who is looking to get into painting or are someone with previous experience looking for inspiration this is the perfect workshop for you.

In this 2 day workshop, you will learn how to create your own stained glass ornament from a selection of provided designs to choose from. Choose between intricate designs that suit your style and personality. Make your glass ornament as perfect decor item to capture the winter sunlight or give it as a gift during the holidays. Artist Derek Currie will guide you through scoring, grinding, foiling, soldering, and finishing your glass artwork. This class is great for beginners with no experience or for those who want to hone their skills in this craft. All tools, equipment, and a variety of glass will be provided.

Inside and outside you can create and draw, don’t let the cooler weather stop you! During this four week course at the Muttart you will have the opportunity to explore materials and see how the world around us can activate our drawings. Artist Andrew Thorne will introduce you to a variety of drawing methods such as xerox transfers, rubbings, and using found elements as a means of mark making and stenciling to generate images. Enjoy spending time in nature and experimenting with your creativity and imagination as you make interesting drawings using a variety of materials such as graphite, pastels, washi papers, printmaking ink, paint, and recycled items. 

All supplies are included, tools and equipment are available for communal use.  An email will be sent out 3 days prior to the program start date to confirm the class.

It is different to draw from life than just using photos. Artist Julie Drew will teach you that what our eyes can see is so much more than a photo can capture. This weekly class at John Janzen Nature Centre will have you experiencing your Sunday mornings seeing and sketching the scenes around you while learning important drawing skills and techniques. Each week you will spend time enjoying nature with a sketchbook and drawing tools in hand. Spend your mornings among nature sketching en plein air (in the open air) and being indoors drawing artifacts from the collection.  
All supplies are included; an email will be sent out 3 days prior to the program start date to confirm the class.
PLEASE NOTE this workshop takes place at the John Janzen Nature Centre and admission is provided in the workshop fee (for the hours of the workshop only, cannot arrive early or stay after).

coursedesc:
Learn how to capture the human form in this 6 week drawing course by drawing from live nude models. Using various drawing tools, you will learn about anatomy, proportion, form, and tone with informative demonstrations from artist Patrick Higgins and from visually studying the live models. Explore drawing with a variety of materials such as graphite, and compressed charcoal as you expand on your drawing skills and work on your observation skills. 

Materials are not included; a supply list will be provided closer to the program start date. 

EXPERIENCE 
This course is great for beginners and those with previous experience looking to improve their skills. 


Materials are not included; a supply list will be provided closer to the program start date.

Focus your study on the portrait and advance your drawing skills during this 6 week course. Through demonstrations and observation of photos, learn the principles of proportion, form, and tonal relationships. Artist Patrick Higgins will guide and teach you to capture the character of the subject with simple drawing materials such as compressed charcoal and pencil. Beginners will have a great time focusing on a particular area of drawing and anyone with previous drawing experience will have the opportunity to explore their own drawing style and gain new knowledge and skills. 

Materials are not included; a supply list will be provided closer to the program start date.

Explore the possibilities with acrylic paint with artist Julie Drew. To begin, gain knowledge in paint and colour by learning about colour mixing and themes. After getting used to brushwork and paint handling, then experiment with adding textures and inclusions: eggshells, sand, and collage elements such as handmade papers and transfer techniques. Make your own creative choices and explore your imagination using acrylic paint. Have the chance to develop your skills as you further your own style and preferences as you explore acrylic paintings with subject matter that inspires you and sparks your creativity. 

NO CLASS NOV 5

Learn how to take great photos in Manual Mode in this two week class! This course will teach you how to use your digital camera's manual mode, which will give you the power to express your artistic creativity in its best light. We will also cover how to use different metering modes and how to read your camera's histogram for perfect exposures everytime.  
Please ensure your camera has the capability to shoot in manual mode. . SUPPLIES Bring your own DSLR camera, full battery, battery charger and lenses.

coursedesc: Learn how to create beautiful portraits of your friends and family using natural light.  We will have an in-class session going into detail on how to photograph portraits, what lenses to use, techniques on photographing using natural light and how to use a reflector.  We also head outdoors to the garden on the roof  to put what we learned in class into practice.  Please bring your camera and charger. Instructor: Reem

Have your child explore their creativity and learn the fundamentals of drawing & painting. Learn and practice various techniques to create beautiful works of art!
 All supplies included.

Learn the fundamentals of drawing cartoons in this comprehensive eight part class!  This course will cover all of the basics of faces, bodies, backgrounds, and colour!  Artists will learn how to draft pictures cleanly and evenly and be challenged to bring as much variety as they can onto a page.  Artists will go home with useful tips and tricks, a sketchbook, full of original pictures, as well as a completed comic book of their own design!  This class is designed to introduce beginner to intermediate artists to the wide world of cartooning and comic art.

 All supplies included.

Students are introduced to the fundamentals of drawing and painting. Translate 3D shapes and objects into masterpieces through the mediums of pencil, pastel, and watercolour. Let’s get creative! All supplies included.
